    • Field Detail

      • attrName

        @ColumnLabel(value="ATTR_NAME")
String attrName
        attribute name.

      • dataType

        @ColumnLabel(value="DATA_TYPE")
int dataType
        attribute type SQL type from Types.

      • attrTypeName

        @ColumnLabel(value="ATTR_TYPE_NAME")
String attrTypeName
        Data source dependent type name. For a UDT, the type name is fully qualified. For a REF, the type name is fully qualified and represents the target type of the reference type.

      • attrSize

        @ColumnLabel(value="ATTR_SIZE")
int attrSize
        column size. For char or date types this is the maximum number of characters; for numeric or decimal types this is precision.

      • decimalDigits

        @ColumnLabel(value="DECIMAL_DIGITS")
Integer decimalDigits
        the number of fractional digits. Null is returned for data types where DECIMAL_DIGITS is not applicable.

      • numPrecRadix

        @ColumnLabel(value="NUM_PREC_RADIX")
int numPrecRadix
        Radix (typically either 10 or 2).

      • nullable

        @ColumnLabel(value="NULLABLE")
int nullable
        whether NULL is allowed.

      • remarks

        @ColumnLabel(value="REMARKS")
@NillableBySpecification
String remarks
        comment describing column.

@NillableBySpecification
String attrDef

      • sourceDataType

        @ColumnLabel(value="SOURCE_DATA_TYPE")
@SuppressionPath(value="attribute/sourceDataType")
@NillableBySpecification
Short sourceDataType

        suppression - the suppression

        attributes - the collection to which retrieved attributes are added.
